The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 SPML net profit jumps 65%

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Feb. 1: Subhash Projects amp; Marketing Limited (SPML) has recorded a 167.4 per cent increase in net sales at Rs 233.91crore in the quarter ended December 31, 2006 against Rs 87.47 crore during the same period last fiscal. Net profit also jumped 65.2 per cent from Rs 5.26 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year to Rs 8.69 crore.

 The board has approved an employee stock option plan (ESOP) and a qualified institutional placement (QIP).

 We have constituted a separate remuneration committee which will work out the details of the ESOP and allocation details would be finalised within a month with the appointment of a merchant banker. For the QIP, we will take a call regarding the dilution and amount in the next three to four months, said Subhash Sethi, vice-chairman and managing director, SPML. 




